# Forbidden vocabulary

`AGENTS.md §4`. CI greps for these terms; matches block merge.

MLM, multi-level, affiliate, referral commission, referral bonus, passive income, earnings, income guarantee, bonus per user, wallet, investment, guaranteed savings, ROI promise, crypto, gambling, casino, betting, adult, firearms.

Allowed: **`Business Introduction`** (singular noun phrase) for the admin-mediated B2B match feature. Never "referral", never "lead", never "partner program" in the affiliate sense.

## Where this applies

Everywhere except `docs/GUARDRAILS.md` (which documents the list itself):

- All user-visible copy (messages/, components, page metadata).
- Code identifiers (variable names, function names, audit-action enums).
- Comments and commit messages.
- Migration file names.
- Branch names.
- Prompts under `prompts/META/` (no escapism — the rule applies to plans too).

## Why these specific terms

- **MLM / multi-level / referral commission / passive income / earnings / income guarantee / bonus per user**: positioning as MLM triggers payment-processor freezes (Stripe explicitly disallows MLM under Restricted Businesses). Even ambiguous wording in marketing can trigger merchant review.
- **Wallet / investment / guaranteed savings / ROI promise**: financial product positioning we are NOT licensed for; SEC / FCA / NBU concerns.
- **Crypto / gambling / casino / betting / adult / firearms**: high-risk verticals Stripe also disallows and Cloudflare Turnstile can refuse service to. The forbidden list is not aesthetic — every entry maps to a real external risk. Adding terms requires an ADR.

## Replacements (suggestion table)

| Forbidden term | Suggested replacement |
| ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------ |
| referral / referral bonus | Business Introduction |
| affiliate program | partner network (only when describing structure) |
| earnings / income | membership benefits |
| wallet | account balance (only for refundable credit) |
| guaranteed | (just remove; never promise) |
| passive income | (remove; not part of the product) |

When in doubt, leave the term out entirely. Rephrasing toward the forbidden term should not be the goal.

